cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.MA 

This paper discusses a distributed resource allocation system for P2P clusters, which involves distributed computing and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of auction-based scheduling algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The use of P2P clusters also involves network infrastructure, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the use of statistical multiplexing, which involves data structures and algorithms, and falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the use of incentives for truth-telling, which falls under the category of cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
